    <title>DAS八月挑战赛——Crypto</title>
    <url>/2021/09/15/DAS%E5%85%AB%E6%9C%88%E6%8C%91%E6%88%98%E8%B5%9B/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<p>DAS八月</p>
<span id="more"></span>
<h1 id="easymath"><a href="#easymath" class="headerlink" title="easymath"></a>easymath</h1><h2 id="task"><a href="#task" class="headerlink" title="task"></a>task</h2><pre><code>assert(len(open(&#39;flag.txt&#39;, &#39;rb&#39;).read()) &lt; 50)
assert(str(int.from_bytes(open(&#39;flag.txt&#39;, &#39;rb&#39;).read(), byteorder=&#39;big&#39;) &lt;&lt; 10000).endswith(&#39;1862790884563160582365888530869690397667546628710795031544304378154769559410473276482265448754388655981091313419549689169381115573539422545933044902527020209259938095466283008&#39;))
</code></pre><h2 id="分析"><a href="#分析" class="headerlink" title="分析"></a>分析</h2><p>题目中给了两个断言。</p>
<p>1.flag的长度小于50。</p>
<p>2.int.from_bytes()函数，是将字符串按照 ascii 码转换成数字。flag转成数字后，再向左移10000，相当于乘以2的10000次方。所以flag的变换就是：</p>
<pre><code>flag * (2 ** 10000) % (10 ** 175) = 1862790884563160582365888530869690397667546628710795031544304378154769559410473276482265448754388655981091313419549689169381115573539422545933044902527020209259938095466283008
</code></pre><p>这里为什么要与 (10 ** 175) 取余呢？，因为最后结尾的数字有175位。举个例子吧</p>
<pre><code>例如有一个数15239971，那么要得到9971，则模10 ** 4
&gt;&gt;&gt; 15239971 % 10**4
9971
</code></pre><h2 id="公式化"><a href="#公式化" class="headerlink" title="公式化"></a>公式化</h2><p>我们设 m = 10 ** 175，余数为r = 186….，则有公式</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{10000} \bmod m=r</script><p>也就是</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{10000}\equiv r\pmod {m}</script><p>同余运算具有同乘性，即两边同乘一个数，表达式仍然成立，那么我们令两边同时乘以$2^{-10000}$ ，左边的就被消去。等式变为</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag\equiv2^{-10000}*r\pmod{m}</script><h3 id="推论"><a href="#推论" class="headerlink" title="推论"></a>推论</h3><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
若a*b\bmod n=1,则\frac{c}{a}\bmod n=c*b\bmod n</script><p>factor分解r</p>
<pre><code>r = 2**178  *  3**2  *  11  *  17  *  31  *  8843778227  *  1368909866633  *  7697795491925421534326846035539558013670970987086177576096701910889341822028986308208879914949
</code></pre><h3 id="化简"><a href="#化简" class="headerlink" title="化简"></a>化简</h3><p>设$r=2^{175}*y$ ，k为除数，则</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{10000} \bmod m=2^{175}*y</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{10000}=k*10^{175}+2^{175}*y</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{10000}=k*5^{175}*2^{175}+2^{175}*y</script><p>同时约去$2^{175}$，得到</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{9825}=k*5^{175}+y</script><p>所以有</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{9825}\bmod 5^{175}=y</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag\equiv2^{-9825}*y\pmod {5^{175}}</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag\bmod 5^{175}=2^{-9825}*y\bmod 5^{175}</script><h3 id="求取逆元"><a href="#求取逆元" class="headerlink" title="求取逆元"></a>求取逆元</h3><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag*2^{9825}\bmod 5^{175}=y</script><p>因为</p>
<pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import gmpy2
&gt;&gt;&gt; gmpy2.gcd(2**9825,5**175)
mpz(1)    #互素
&gt;&gt;&gt; gmpy2.invert(2**9825,5**175)
mpz(37060642858830709134940196867045973227403060275045262619551322094165830229956154872900603295338708950615820792866958796943)
</code></pre><p>所以存在逆元d，则</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
d*flag*2^{9825}\bmod 5^{175}=y*d</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
d*2^{9825}\bmod 5^{175}=1</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag\bmod 5^{175}=y*d</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
flag\equiv y*d\pmod {5^{175}}</script><h2 id="exp"><a href="#exp" class="headerlink" title="exp"></a>exp</h2><pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import gmpy2
&gt;&gt;&gt; from Crypto.Util.number import *
&gt;&gt;&gt; d = gmpy2.invert(2**9825,5**175)
&gt;&gt;&gt; r = 1862790884563160582365888530869690397667546628710795031544304378154769559410473276482265448754388655981091313419549689169381115573539422545933044902527020209259938095466283008
&gt;&gt;&gt; y = r // 2**175
&gt;&gt;&gt; flag = (y*d)%(5**175)
&gt;&gt;&gt; print(long_to_bytes(flag))
b&#39;flag&#123;90ee7e8df270bf5133a95ff904a059b8&#125;&#39;
</code></pre><p>另一种，当$r=2^{178}*y$ </p>
<pre><code>&gt;&gt;&gt; import gmpy2
&gt;&gt;&gt; from Crypto.Util.number import *
&gt;&gt;&gt; gmpy2.gcd(2**9822,5**175)
mpz(1)
&gt;&gt;&gt; d = gmpy2.invert(2**9822,5**175)
&gt;&gt;&gt; r = 1862790884563160582365888530869690397667546628710795031544304378154769559410473276482265448754388655981091313419549689169381115573539422545933044902527020209259938095466283008
&gt;&gt;&gt; y = r // 2**178
&gt;&gt;&gt; flag = (y*d)%(5**175)
&gt;&gt;&gt; print(long_to_bytes(flag))
b&#39;flag&#123;90ee7e8df270bf5133a95ff904a059b8&#125;&#39;
</code></pre><h1 id="let’s-play-with-rsa"><a href="#let’s-play-with-rsa" class="headerlink" title="let’s play with rsa~"></a>let’s play with rsa~</h1><h2 id="task-1"><a href="#task-1" class="headerlink" title="task"></a>task</h2><pre><code>from sympy import isprime,nextprime
from Crypto.Util.number import getPrime as getprime ,long_to_bytes,bytes_to_long,inverse
flag=&#39;flag&#123;***************&#125;&#39;

def play():
    p=getprime(1024)
    q=getprime(1024)

    n=p*q
    e=65537

    print &quot;Hello,let&#39;s play rsa~\n&quot;
    print &#39;Now,I make some numbers,wait a second\n&#39;
    n1=getprime(200)
    n2=getprime(200)
    number=n1*n2
    print &quot;Ok,i will send two numbers to you,one of them was encoded.\n&quot;
    print &quot;Encode n1:%d,\n&quot;%(pow(n1,e,n))
    print &quot;And n2:%d.\n&quot;%n2

    print &quot;Information that can now be made public:the public key (n,e):(%d,%d)\n&quot;%(n,e)
    while True:
        try:
            c=int(raw_input(&quot;ok,now,tell me the value of the number (encode it for safe):&quot;))
        except:
            print &quot;Sorry,the input is illeagal, and the integer is accept~&quot;
        else:
            break
    d=inverse(e,(p-1)*(q-1))
    m=pow(c,d,n)
    if m==number:
        print &quot;It&#39;s easy and interesting,didn&#39;t it?\n&quot;
        print &quot;This is the gift for you :&quot;+flag
    else:
        print &quot;Emmmmm,there is something wrong, bye~\n&quot;

if __name__ == &#39;__main__&#39;:
    play()
</code></pre><h3 id="分析-1"><a href="#分析-1" class="headerlink" title="分析"></a>分析</h3><p>已知</p>
<pre><code>设c1 = pow(n1,e,n) #也就是题目给的n1
n2 
n = p*q 
e
</code></pre><p>输入</p>
<pre><code>需要输入c，使 pow(c,d,n) == n1 * n2，输出flag
</code></pre><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
n_1^e\bmod n=c_1</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
c^d\bmod n=m=n_1*n_2</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
m^e\bmod n=c</script><p>所以</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
(n_1*n_2)^e\bmod n=c</script><p>根据模运算规则化简</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
( a * b ) \bmod p=[(a\bmod p)*(b\bmod p)]\bmod p</script><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
c=(n_1^e*n_2^e)\bmod n=[(n_1^e\bmod n)*(n_2^e\bmod n)]\bmod n</script><p>是不是很眼熟？$n_1^e\bmod n=c_1$ 我们已经知道，所以化简得到最终结果</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
c=(n_1^e*n_2^e)\bmod n=[c_1*(n_2^e\bmod n)]\bmod n</script><p>再看右边，所有元素都已知，就可求出c。</p>
<p>连接靶机后得到</p>
<pre><code>Hello,let&#39;s play rsa~

Now,I make some numbers,wait a second

Ok,i will send two numbers to you,one of them was encoded.

Encode n1:,

And n2:817883629056426050889438610854875115586179937771656074400107.

Information that can now be made public:the public key (n,e):(,65537)

ok,now,tell me the value of the number (encode it for safe):
</code></pre><p>输入正确答案后</p>
<pre><code>Hello,let&#39;s play rsa~

Now,I make some numbers,wait a second

Ok,i will send two numbers to you,one of them was encoded.

Encode n1:,

And n2:817883629056426050889438610854875115586179937771656074400107.

Information that can now be made public:the public key (n,e):(,65537)

ok,now,tell me the value of the number (encode it for safe):
It&#39;s easy and interesting,didn&#39;t it?

This is the gift for you :flag&#123;eca6741f-2746-4983-8e33-4c539570b885&#125;Hello,let&#39;s play rsa~

Now,I make some numbers,wait a second

Ok,i will send two numbers to you,one of them was encoded.

Encode n1:,

And n2:817883629056426050889438610854875115586179937771656074400107.

Information that can now be made public:the public key (n,e):(,65537)

ok,now,tell me the value of the number (encode it for safe):
It&#39;s easy and interesting,didn&#39;t it?

This is the gift for you :flag&#123;eca6741f-2746-4983-8e33-4c539570b885&#125;
</code></pre><h2 id="exp-1"><a href="#exp-1" class="headerlink" title="exp"></a>exp</h2><pre><code>n2 =817883629056426050889438610854875115586179937771656074400107
n 
e =65537
c1 
c = (c1*(n2**e)%n)%n
print(c)
</code></pre><h1 id="ezRSA"><a href="#ezRSA" class="headerlink" title="ezRSA"></a>ezRSA</h1><h2 id="task-2"><a href="#task-2" class="headerlink" title="task"></a>task</h2><pre><code>from secret import flag
from Crypto.Util.number import *
from random import getrandbits
from hashlib import sha256

class EzRsa:
    def __init__(self):
        self.E = 0x10001
        self.P = getPrime(1024)
        self.Q = getPrime(1024)
        while GCD((self.P-1)*(self.Q-1), self.E) != 1:
            self.Q = getPrime(1024)
        self.N = self.P*self.Q

    def encrypt(self):
        f = getrandbits(32)
        c = pow(f, self.E, self.N)
        return (f, c)

    def encrypt_flag(self, flag):
        f = bytes_to_long(flag)
        c = pow(f, self.E, self.N)
        return c

def proof():
    seed = getrandbits(32)
    print(seed)
    sha = sha256(str(seed).encode()).hexdigest()#将seed进行sha256加密
    print(f&quot;sha256(&#123;seed&gt;&gt;18&#125;...).hexdigest() = &#123;sha&#125;&quot;)
    sha_i = input(&quot;plz enter seed: &quot;)
    if sha256(sha_i.encode()).hexdigest() != sha:
